HEADWORD: abigail
<hw>ab"i*gail</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The proper name
used as an appellative.]</ety> <def>A lady's waiting-maid.</def>
<rj><au>Pepys.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her <qex>abigail</qex> reported that Mrs. Gutheridge had a set of
night curls for sleeping in.</q> <rj><qau>Leslie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abiliment</ent>⟦br⟧
